This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during the swearing-in ceremony of Eugene Scalia as the new Secretary of Labor. President Trump praises Scalia's qualifications and emphasizes his commitment to American workers. The President also mentions Scalia's family members who attended the ceremony. Additionally, President Trump addresses the issue of the whistleblower and the controversy surrounding his phone call with the President of Ukraine. He criticizes the whistleblower's report and accuses Congressman Adam Schiff of making up a phony call. The President expresses his determination to uncover corruption related to the 2016 election.